text.tspan: The Church — Building by the Growth in Life
Drawn by Him each morning at His dear face we gaze,
Sitting at His feet each day His speaking we heed,
Then in Him we’re living, Him to others shining,
Bearing fruit we’re filled with joy indeed!
Holding truth in love we’re growing up into Christ,
Honouring each other, that we’re members we prove;
Through the cross, by Spirit, Christ we are dispensing,
Blended as the one new man we move.
House to house we’re practising the Body life,
We in life are reigning as His loving bride;
Here we have the foretaste of our destiny—
